CNCP v1 25627
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8868: Scoped style attribute not attached to selector key if it's a pseudo-class/element",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:59.171564+00:00",
  "text": "Scoped style attribute not attached to selector key if it's a pseudo-class/element\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.3.9\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\n[https://play.vuejs.org example](https://play.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a scoped style block.\r\n2. Add a rule set with a selector which has any ancestor selectors and a bare pseudo-class (but not `:is()` or `:where()`) as the key (e.g. `div :not(.test)` not `div *:not(.test)`).\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<style scoped>\r\ndiv :not(.test) {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv :required {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n\r\n/* workaround: add `*` to the pseudo class */\r\ndiv *:required {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n</style>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nThe generated CSS rule set's selector list is scoped to the key of the selector (i.e. `div [data-v-7ba5bd90]:not(.test)`) _even if the key is a bare pseudo-class or pseudo-element_ (except in the case of `:deep`).\r\n\r\n```css\r\ndiv [data-v-7ba5bd90]:not(.test) {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv [data-v-7ba5bd90]:required {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv *[data-v-7ba5bd90]:required {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nThe generated CSS rule set's selector list is scoped to the last selector part that is not a bare pseudo-class (i.e. `div[data-v-7ba5bd90] :not(.test)`).\r\n\r\n```css\r\ndiv[data-v-7ba5bd90] :not(.test) {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv[data-v-7ba5bd90] :required {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv *[data-v-7ba5bd90]:required {\r\n  color: tomato;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis leads to styles unintentionally leaking out of the scoped tree.\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nBinaries:\r\n    Node: 19.1.0 - C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\node.EXE\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.19 - C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\yarn.CMD\r\n    npm: 9.8.0 - ~\\dev\\package\\node_modules\\.bin\\npm.CMD\r\n    pnpm: 8.5.1 - C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\pnpm.CMD\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Edge: Spartan (44.22621.1992.0), Chromium (115.0.1901.183)\r\n    Internet Explorer: 11.0.22621.1\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n- This seems to be true for _most_ pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements, but isn't true for `:is()`, `:where()`, and the special case `:deep()`\r\n- Initially posted as a question here: https://github.com/vuejs/core/discussions/8800\r\n- The current behavior is unexpected to me when writing scoped styles as it easily allows styles to leak out of the scoped tree (e.g. when using slots)",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: compiler",
    "scope: sfc",
    "has workaround",
    "has PR",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
